# StageSync v5 ÔÇö Constitution

## Single source of truth (SSOT)

- **Server authority**: transport, project state, and timing decisions live on `@stagesync/server`. Clients must not invent authoritative clock or song state.
- **Client playhead**: the web client may **smooth / interpolate the playhead between server ticks only**. It must not advance authoritative musical time independently of the server.

## Monorepo boundaries

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `apps/server` | Express API, persistence, transport SSOT |
| `apps/web` | Vite + React client (UI only; no authoritative time) |
| `packages/shared` | Pure domain: Zod schemas, time helpers ÔÇö no DOM, no Node FS |
| `packages/ui` | Design-system primitives (`Button`, tokens) ÔÇö no business logic |
| `packages/eslint-config` / `typescript-config` | Tooling only |
| `data/` | Local runtime layout (templates + gitkeeps; user data gitignored) |

Do not cross boundaries: UI must not import server; shared must stay pure; apps depend on packages, not the reverse.

## Pure time

- Musical / beat time math lives in `@stagesync/shared` as **pure functions** (deterministic, side-effect free).
- No `Date.now()` / `performance.now()` inside shared time helpers for domain conversion ÔÇö callers pass clocks/ticks in.

## Validation (Zod)

- Validate at **edges** (HTTP body, file load, IPC) with Zod from `@stagesync/shared`.
- **Fail fast**: reject invalid payloads; do not silently coerce away required shape.

## UI ÔÇö Button & tokens

- Canonical `Button` exposes a **closed set of 7 interaction states**: default, hover, focus, active, disabled, loading, selected.
- Colors and spacing use **`--ss-*` CSS variables** only (`packages/ui` tokens). No ad-hoc HEX in components.

## Data layout

```
data/
  library/          # library index (+ library.template.json)
  projects/<id>/    # per-project files
  logs/             # runtime logs (gitignored content)
```

See `docs/adr/0001-storage-layout.md`.

## Commits

- [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) only (commitlint + husky).
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `chore`, `refactor`, `test`, `ci`, ÔÇª
- Do not use `--no-verify` in normal workflow. See `CONTRIBUTING.md`.

## Out of scope (v5 day-0 / alpha)

Do **not** add without an explicit product decision:

- Admin / hygiene HTTP UI for storage scrubbing
- Dual write paths to legacy 4.x database shapes
- New Button variants outside the closed set
- Client-authoritative transport or MIDI clock
- Pushing secrets, local `data/projects/*` user content, or `node_modules` to git
